# OKDR Review Site

Static review mockups for the proposed unified OKDR (Okinawa Kobudo Doushi Rensei-Kai) + Authentic Ancient Arts website redesign. Two self-contained HTML files deployed to DigitalOcean App Platform via GitHub. This is a stakeholder review site — not the production Flask app.

## Files

- `index.html` — OKDR home page (kobudo HQ framing, AAA dojo as honbu)
- `karate.html` — Shorin-Ryu Shorinkan karate detail page
- Both pages cross-link via nav, breadcrumb, and footer
- The OKDR crest is embedded as a base64 data URI in each file (~200KB each — intentional, keeps files portable)

## Hard constraints

- Static HTML only. No build step. No package.json. No framework.
- Do not extract CSS into separate files. Each HTML page is intentionally self-contained.
- Do not restructure, refactor, or "improve" the design. It has been iteratively approved by the user and stakeholders.
- Do not add dependencies or tooling beyond what is needed for deploy.
- Do not extend this toward the production Flask/Jinja2 app — that comes later.
- Python only for any scripting or tooling (per user's stack preference).

## Design and content conventions

- Preserve gold (kobudo) / red (karate) color coding throughout.
- When editing content, update placeholder member dojo data only when the user provides real info.
- After any filename or link change, verify cross-page links still work (`index.html` ↔ `karate.html`).
- Link targets use `index.html`, `karate.html`, and anchor hashes (e.g. `index.html#honbu`) — not old names like `OKDR-mockup.html`.

## Deployment

- Push to `main` on GitHub; DO App Platform auto-deploys as a static site (~30s).
- No build command. Output directory is `/`. Index document is `index.html`.

## Pending placeholders (need real data from Sensei)

- Member dojos: Chicago "Midwest Karate Academy" and Naha "Naha Dojo Affiliate" are placeholders. AAA (Waukesha) and Eastwind (Canada) are real.
- Karate page curriculum: kata names are canonical Shorinkan progression — verify with Sensei.
- Class schedule: placeholder times — get the real schedule.
- Open question: Should a parallel Kobudo detail page be built (matching karate.html depth)?

## When making edits

- Keep changes minimal and scoped to what was requested.
- Edit HTML directly; commit and push when the user asks.
- Keep it boring. Boring deploys reliably.
